Animation Library Reference

This page provides a comprehensive reference of all available animations in Meshy's Auto-Rigging & Animation API. Each animation is identified by a unique action_id that can be used when creating animation tasks.

Available Animations

Below is a complete list of animations available for use with the Auto-Rigging & Animation API. Use the action_id value when creating an animation task with the POST /openapi/v1/animations endpoint.

Usage Example

To apply an animation to your rigged character, use the action_id in your API request:

const payload = {
  rig_task_id: "YOUR_RIGGING_TASK_ID",
  action_id: 92,  // Double Combo Attack animation
};

// Send this payload to the POST /openapi/v1/animations endpoint

For more details on how to create animation tasks, see the Auto-Rigging & Animation API documentation.
